<paragraph id="D6E0846B18CA5E62C8A60501C77854AE" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Greece, Peloponnes Province: Arcadia, Parnon, 4 km WSW Kastanitsa, 37.28333 /22.66666, 550-600 m a.s.l (please see note below for altitude estimations).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4173A68640F349C0C9EB35131D79573D" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C6D4DF1287EEC56AF7B39F60E4CEB792" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="24AF9685A1A0B99F2A9ABB9F0AAD77A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<taxonomicName id="3910B9A84F0AE11AACE605BCC2CCA288" authority="Mayr, 1861" authorityName="Salata &amp; Borowiec" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Temnothorax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Temnothorax parnonensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parnonensis">
<emphasis id="C17AB3CD2DFEFD7F6BFAE958DDA892CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Temnothorax parnonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
well differs from other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="FAB1D8A3573A32B0932E7DEF5AF6A3EC" genus="T." lsidName="T. anodontoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="anodontoides">
<emphasis id="27B95BAECC0F64CCA399FACB560F00B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">T. anodontoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the reduced head sculpture, with presence of smooth or indistinctly microreticulate patch on the central part of frons, and brighter yellowish brown to brown body coloration (remaining members of the group have frons entirely sculptured and darker body coloration).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
